## 1. What is this Project?

> **In simple words:** A College ERP is a web-based software that **replaces manual college work** like attendance registers, mark sheets, and notice boards with a digital, always-available system.

**Three types of users use this system:**

| User | What they can do |
|------|-----------------|
| 👨‍💼 **Admin** | Manage departments, teachers, students, courses, timetable |
| 👨‍🏫 **Faculty/Teacher** | Take attendance, create assignments/tests, post notices |
| 👨‍🎓 **Student** | View attendance, marks, timetable, fee status, assignments |

---

## 2. Why We Built It? (Problem Statement)

**Problems in traditional college systems:**
- Attendance taken on paper → data gets lost
- Students don't know their attendance % until end of semester
- Notice boards are hard to see and go unread
- Admin does repetitive data entry every year for new students
- No central place to view marks, fee, timetable

**Our Solution:**
- Digital attendance system → real-time tracking
- Students can see their attendance anytime on their dashboard
- Notices are pushed to specific departments or all users
- Admin promotes students to next semester in one click
- Every user sees their data in a personalized, role-based dashboard

---

## 3. System Architecture (Big Picture)

The system is split into **3 tiers:**

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│         USER'S WEB BROWSER                       │
│   React App (what user sees & clicks)            │
│   Port: 5173                                     │
└────────────────────┬────────────────────────────┘
                     │  HTTP Requests (Axios)
                     │  + WebSocket (Socket.io)
┌────────────────────▼────────────────────────────┐
│         BACKEND SERVER                           │
│   Node.js + Express.js API                       │
│   Handles all logic & security                   │
│   Port: 3000                                     │
└────────────────────┬────────────────────────────┘
                     │  SQL Queries
┌────────────────────▼────────────────────────────┐
│         DATABASE                                 │
│   MySQL → clg_db                                 │
│   Stores all permanent data                      │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

> **Key point for teachers:** Frontend never touches the database directly. It always goes through the backend (API). This is the standard 3-tier architecture.

