## 4. FRONTEND

> **Technology:** React 18 + TypeScript + TailwindCSS + Vite

### What does the Frontend do?
- Shows the user interface (login page, dashboards, tables, forms)
- Sends requests to the backend API when user takes an action
- Updates the screen when it gets data back

### Folder Structure (Important files only)
```
frontend/app/src/
│
├── main.tsx           ← Starting point of the app
├── App.tsx            ← Sets up providers (Auth, Theme, Socket)
├── routes.tsx         ← Defines which page to show for which URL
│
├── pages/             ← Full page components
│   ├── Login.tsx
│   ├── AdminDashboard.tsx
│   ├── StudentDashboard.tsx
│   └── FacultyDashboard.tsx
│
├── sections/          ← Sub-sections inside Admin dashboard
│   ├── ManageStudents.tsx
│   ├── ManageTeachers.tsx
│   ├── ManageCourses.tsx
│   ├── ManageDepartments.tsx
│   ├── TimetableManagement.tsx
│   ├── ManageEssentialLinks.tsx
│   └── StudentStatusManagement.tsx
│
├── components/        ← Reusable UI building blocks
│   ├── common/        ← DataTable, Modal, FormInput, etc.
│   ├── student/       ← StudentProfileCard, AttendanceBar, etc.
│   └── faculty/       ← AssignmentSection, UnitTestsSection, etc.
│
├── context/           ← Global state (shared across all pages)
│   ├── AuthContext.tsx    ← Logged-in user info
│   ├── ThemeContext.tsx   ← Dark/Light mode
│   └── SocketContext.tsx  ← Real-time updates (WebSocket)
│
├── api/               ← All network calls to backend
│   ├── axios.ts       ← Configured Axios with auto token refresh
│   ├── auth.ts        ← Login, logout, get user
│   ├── students.ts    ← Admin student operations
│   ├── teachers.ts    ← Admin teacher operations
│   ├── courses.ts     ← Admin course operations
│   ├── faculty.ts     ← Faculty dashboard + attendance + marks
│   └── notices.ts     ← Notice operations
│
├── hooks/             ← Custom React hooks (fetch + state logic)
│   ├── useStudents.ts
│   ├── useTeachers.ts
│   ├── useCourses.ts
│   └── useTimetable.ts
│
└── types/
    └── index.ts       ← All TypeScript data types (77 interfaces)
```

### How Routing works
```
URL path             → Component shown       → Who can access
/login               → Login page            → Everyone
/admin               → AdminDashboard        → Admin only
/student/dashboard   → StudentDashboard      → Students only
/teacher/dashboard   → FacultyDashboard      → Faculty only
/unauthorized        → 403 error page        → If wrong role
*                    → 404 not found page    → Unknown URL
```

**ProtectedRoute** component checks if the user is logged in AND has the correct role before showing the page.

### Context (Global State) Explanation
| Context | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `AuthContext` | Stores logged-in user, role, JWT token. Provides `login()`, `logout()` |
| `ThemeContext` | Dark/Light mode toggle, persists in localStorage |
| `SocketContext` | Connects to backend via WebSocket. When DB changes → refreshes UI |

### How API calls work (Axios)
1. User clicks a button → frontend calls an API function
2. `axios.ts` automatically attaches the **JWT token** to the request header
3. If token expired → silently gets a new one (**token refresh**)
4. If still unauthorized → redirects to login

