## 5. BACKEND

> **Technology:** Node.js + Express 5 + mysql2/promise + jsonwebtoken + bcrypt

### What does the Backend do?
- Receives requests from frontend
- Validates who sent the request (authentication)
- Checks if they have permission (authorization)
- Runs database queries
- Sends back the result as JSON

### Folder Structure
```
backend/
│
├── index.js           ← Entry point: starts server, sets up routes
│
├── config/
│   └── connect_db.js  ← MySQL connection pool (max 10 connections)
│
├── middleware/
│   ├── auth.js        ← Checks JWT token (authenticate)
│   └── authorize.js   ← Checks user role (authorize)
│
└── routes/
    ├── auth.js        ← /login, /logout, /refresh, /me
    ├── admin.js       ← /admin/... (all admin operations)
    ├── student.js     ← /student/... (student data)
    └── teacher.js     ← /teacher/... (faculty operations)
```

### Route Overview (What APIs exist)

#### 🔐 Auth Routes (`/login`)
| Method | URL | What it does |
|--------|-----|-------------|
| POST | `/login` | Login with email + password |
| POST | `/login/logout` | Logout (clears session) |
| POST | `/login/refresh` | Get new access token silently |
| GET | `/login/me` | Get current logged-in user's profile |

#### 👨‍💼 Admin Routes (`/admin`)
| Method | URL | What it does |
|--------|-----|-------------|
| GET | `/admin/departments` | List all departments |
| POST | `/admin/create_department` | Add new department |
| GET | `/admin/filter_students` | List students (with filters) |
| POST | `/admin/create_student` | Create student + auto-enroll |
| GET | `/admin/filter_teachers` | List teachers |
| POST | `/admin/create_teacher` | Create teacher account |
| GET | `/admin/filter_courses` | List courses |
| POST | `/admin/create_course` | Add new course |
| GET | `/admin/timetable` | Get timetable grid |
| POST | `/admin/timetable` | Add timetable entry |
| POST | `/admin/promote_students` | Promote students to next semester |
| PUT | `/admin/students/:id/mark_dc` | Mark student as detained |
| GET | `/admin/departments/total` | Count of departments (for stats) |

#### 👨‍🏫 Teacher/Faculty Routes (`/teacher`)
| Method | URL | What it does |
|--------|-----|-------------|
| GET | `/teacher/dashboard` | Full faculty dashboard data |
| POST | `/teacher/notices` | Post a notice |
| POST | `/teacher/attendance/session` | Start an attendance session |
| GET | `/teacher/attendance/session/:id/students` | Get students for session |
| POST | `/teacher/attendance/submit` | Save attendance |
| POST | `/teacher/assignments` | Create new assignment |
| GET | `/teacher/assignments/:courseId` | List assignments for course |
| POST | `/teacher/tests` | Create unit test |
| POST | `/teacher/tests/:id/scores` | Submit test scores |
| GET | `/teacher/internal-marks/calculate/:courseId` | Calculate internal marks |

#### 👨‍🎓 Student Routes (`/student`)
| Method | URL | What it does |
|--------|-----|-------------|
| GET | `/student/dashboard` | All student dashboard data in one call |
| GET | `/student/notices/recent` | Recent notices for the student |

### Middleware (How security works)
```
Request comes in
     ↓
authenticate()     ← Checks JWT token is valid
     ↓  
authorize("role")  ← Checks if user's role matches
     ↓
Route handler runs ← Actual logic executes
     ↓
Response sent back
```

### Real-time Updates (Socket.io)
- When any **POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE** request succeeds on the backend, it emits a `db_change` event via WebSocket
- All connected browsers receive this event
- Their UI automatically refreshes to show new data
- This means if Admin adds a student while Teacher is online, Teacher's student count updates **without refreshing the page**

